    "topicLabel": "Biodiversity",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "calculator": false,
    "isLatex": false,
    "format": "text",
    "question": "A tropical rainforest and a temperate grassland each contain 200 individual organisms, but the rainforest has 40 different species while the grassland has only 8 different species. Which conclusion is most accurate?",
    "choices": [
      "A) The temperate grassland has greater biodiversity because its species are better adapted to survive in harsher conditions",
      "B) The two ecosystems have equal biodiversity because they contain the same number of individual organisms",
      "C) The tropical rainforest has greater species richness, which is one component of biodiversity indicating more variety among organisms",
      "D) The tropical rainforest has greater biodiversity only if the species are evenly distributed among individuals"
    ],
    "answer": 2,
