    "explanation": "A keystone species has a disproportionately large effect on its ecosystem relative to its abundance or biomass. Sea otters regulate sea urchin populations, which in turn allows kelp to thrive. Option B is incorrect because keystone species are typically not the most abundant - abundance defines dominant species, not keystone species. Option C is incorrect because sea otters do not control physical abiotic factors like temperature. Option D is incorrect because indicator species signal environmental conditions but do not structurally control community composition the way a keystone species does."
