    "question": "In a rocky intertidal ecosystem, sea otters prey heavily on sea urchins, which in turn consume kelp. When sea otter populations collapse due to hunting, sea urchin populations explode and kelp forests are destroyed, eliminating habitat for dozens of fish and invertebrate species. Which of the following statements best explains why this outcome demonstrates a trophic cascade rather than simply predator-prey dynamics, and what it reveals about biodiversity?",
