    "difficulty": "medium",
    "calculator": false,
    "isLatex": false,
    "format": "text",
    "question": "A wildlife biologist studying two species records the following: Species X produces few offspring, provides extensive parental care, and most individuals survive to old age before dying. Species Y produces thousands of offspring with no parental care, and most offspring die early in life. Which survivorship curve types match Species X and Species Y, respectively?",
    "choices": [
      "A) Type I and Type III",
      "B) Type III and Type I",
      "C) Type II and Type III",
      "D) Type I and Type II"
    ],
