    "question": "After Corporate Average Fuel Economy (CAFE) standards were significantly tightened, total U.S. gasoline consumption did not decrease as much as engineers had projected based solely on the improved vehicle efficiency. Which of the following phenomena most directly explains this discrepancy, and what does it imply about relying exclusively on efficiency improvements as an environmental policy?",
