    "explanation": "SO2 and NOx are primary pollutants emitted directly from combustion sources. In the atmosphere, they undergo chemical reactions with water, oxygen, and oxidants to form sulfuric acid (H2SO4) and nitric acid (HNO3), which are secondary pollutants. These acids fall as wet or dry deposition onto soils in the watershed. In soils with low buffering capacity, the acids leach through and drain into lakes, lowering lake pH and harming aquatic life even without direct deposition onto the lake surface. Option A incorrectly states that SO2 and NOx dissolve directly into lakes as acid rain - SO2 and NOx must first be chemically transformed into acids in the atmosphere. Option C incorrectly classifies sulfuric and nitric acid as primary pollutants; they are secondary. Option D fabricates a mechanism in which NOx and SO2 react with ground-level ozone to form acid rain - this is not the actual chemical pathway; ozone is not a direct reactant in acid rain formation."
