    "question": "A city located in a valley experiences a night of clear skies and calm winds following several days of industrial activity. By the next morning, residents report unusually high concentrations of ground-level pollutants and reduced visibility. Which of the following best explains why the thermal inversion that formed overnight is MORE persistent and MORE severe in this location compared to a city on a flat coastal plain?",
