    "question": "A coal-burning power plant in the midwestern United States installs scrubbers that remove 95% of sulfur dioxide (SO2) emissions. Despite this, ecologists in a downwind northeastern state report continued acidification of lakes. Which of the following best explains why lake acidification persists, and what additional factor must be considered?",
