    "question": "A large hypoxic zone has developed at the mouth of a river delta emptying into a coastal ocean. Scientists measure extremely low dissolved oxygen levels near the bottom sediments but near-normal oxygen levels at the surface. Which of the following best explains this vertical oxygen gradient and identifies the primary driver of bottom-water hypoxia?",
