    "question": "A coastal estuary near a heavily farmed watershed begins experiencing massive algal blooms each summer, followed by large fish kills. A researcher measures dissolved oxygen levels near the seafloor at 1.5 mg/L. Which sequence of events most accurately explains the fish kills, and what is the PRIMARY nutrient driving this process in most coastal marine systems?",
