    "difficulty": "medium",
    "calculator": false,
    "isLatex": false,
    "format": "text",
    "question": "Researchers monitoring a coral reef ecosystem document declining coral cover over several decades. Which chemical process most directly links increased atmospheric CO2 to this coral decline?",
    "choices": [
      "A) Increased CO2 raises ocean temperatures, causing corals to expel their symbiotic algae and bleach.",
      "B) CO2 dissolves in seawater to form carbonic acid, lowering pH and reducing carbonate ions needed for coral skeleton formation.",
      "C) CO2 increases dissolved oxygen in ocean water, promoting the growth of algae that outcompete corals.",
      "D) Elevated CO2 increases the solubility of calcium in seawater, which inhibits the biochemical pathways corals use to build reefs."
    ],
    "answer": 1,
