    "answer": 0,
    "explanation": "Both permafrost thaw and albedo reduction are positive feedback loops. Permafrost thaw releases CH4 and CO2, greenhouse gases that trap more heat, which causes more warming and more thaw - a self-reinforcing cycle. Reduced albedo (darker ocean and land replacing white ice) means more solar radiation is absorbed rather than reflected, further increasing temperatures. Option B is a common trap: students often confuse 'reflecting less energy' with a negative feedback, but less reflection means more absorption and more warming, which is amplifying (positive). Option C incorrectly frames both as negative feedbacks. Option D reverses the classification of permafrost thaw entirely."
