    "question": "A government implements a cap-and-trade program to reduce industrial CO2 emissions. In the first year, Company A reduces its emissions well below its permit allocation and sells its surplus permits to Company B, which cannot meet its reduction targets cost-effectively. Critics argue this system allows wealthy companies to simply 'buy their way out' of reducing emissions. Which of the following best evaluates both the validity of this criticism and the overall environmental effectiveness of the program?",
