    "question": "Sea otters are often cited as a keystone species in kelp forest ecosystems because they prey on sea urchins, preventing overgrazing of kelp. A researcher claims that sea otters have a disproportionately large effect on kelp forest structure relative to their biomass. Which of the following findings would most directly undermine this keystone species claim?",
