    "question": "A logistic growth model describes a population that has now reached 80% of its carrying capacity (K). Which of the following most accurately describes what will happen to the per capita growth rate and the total number of individuals added to the population per year, compared to when the population was at 50% of carrying capacity (K/2)?",
