    "question": "A student makes the following claim: 'Coastal upwelling is common along eastern boundary ocean coastlines (western coastlines of continents, such as Peru and California) because the Coriolis effect directly pulls cold, nutrient-rich water up from the deep ocean to replace surface water that has been pushed offshore.' Which of the following best evaluates the student's claim?",
