      "B) The location described is correct, but upwelling is driven through the intermediate mechanism of Ekman transport, which is itself driven by the Coriolis effect — not by the Coriolis effect acting directly on deep water.",
      "C) The location described is incorrect — upwelling occurs along western boundary ocean coastlines (eastern coastlines of continents), and it is driven by Ekman transport.",
