      "B) Deforestation causes regional warming and drying primarily because reduced evapotranspiration decreases latent heat flux and atmospheric moisture recycling, while loss of biomass releases stored carbon.",
      "C) Deforestation causes regional cooling because the exposed soil and pasture surface reflects significantly more incoming shortwave radiation than the original forest canopy, reducing net surface energy absorption.",
