      "C) CFCs rise into the stratosphere and directly absorb UV radiation that would otherwise break apart ozone, reducing ozone concentrations over time. The Montreal Protocol required all nations to switch from CFCs to HFCs within five years of signing.",
      "D) CFCs release chlorine that reacts with ozone to form ClO, but ClO is quickly sequestered by stratospheric reactions and does not continue a catalytic chain, so CFC impacts are self-limiting. The Montreal Protocol required all nations, including developing nations, to immediately cease all CFC production."
